<div class="article-content">

<h1 class="article">May hits back as governmnet fails to address local&nbsp;train</h1>


<p class="published">18 July 2006</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>The Government has refused to reply to specific concerns raised in writing by Theresa May MP regarding the rail service to Maidenhead and Twyford.</p>

	<p>Theresa May wrote in March to the Department for Transport calling for a full reinstatement of all fast and semi-fast services that had been removed from the First Great Western draft December 2006 timetable.</p>

	<p>The Department replied to Theresa on the 12th June. In response to their letter, Theresa May said:</p>

	<p><em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;Instead of getting a full response from the Department, I received a standard letter, pointing me in the direction of two announcements <span class="caps">FGW</span> had made in April and June. I was eager to read these announcements to see if our concerns had been fully addressed by the department. Unfortunately I was severely disappointed. Although April&acirc;&#128;&#153;s announcement proudly heralded the reinstatement of one service from Twyford to London Paddington, the July announcement appeared to be nothing to do with Maidenhead at all &acirc;&#128;&#147; it detailed additional services on the South Coast!</em></p>

	<p><em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;This is just a further example of how the Government has lost touch with the citizens of Maidenhead &acirc;&#128;&#147; after all, they should at least know we&acirc;&#128;&#153;re not on the South Coast!</em></p>

	<p><em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;Furthermore, the letter announces that, &acirc;&#128;&#152;many of the local services have been reinstated&acirc;&#128;&#153;. This is simply not true. One new train has been introduced and one has been reinstated.</em></p>

	<p><em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;They consider that this improvement &acirc;&#128;&#152;successfully balances competing demands&acirc;&#128;&#153; for their service. This is again a falsehood. They will not satisfy the demands of the thousands of Maidenhead commuters until they reinstate all mainline fast and semi-fast services.&rsquo;</em></p>
</div>
<p class="article-category" style="display:none;">Trains, Services</p>
</div>
