<div class="article-content">

<h1 class="article">May celebrates trains campaign success for&nbsp;Twyford</h1>


<p class="published">28 July 2006</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>First Great Western have told local MP Theresa May that they have agreed to reinstate the 0727 from Twford to London Paddington.</p>

	<p>Richard Green at the First Group confirmed that the new 0726 was effectively a reinstatement of the 0727. He also admitted that this development was a direct result of the consultation period with local commuters and Theresa May.</p>

	<p>Theresa May said, <em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;First Great Western have had to listen to the needs of the Tywford and Maidenhead commuter. We have fiercely campaigned for the reinstatement of the 0726 and this is a real win for the local community.</em></p>

	<p><em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;However, there is still a long way to go; the campaign is by no means over. I will continue to press First Great western for the reinstatement of all fast and semi-fast services from Twyford and Maidenhead.&acirc;&#128;&#153;</em></p>
</div>
