<a href='http://www.tmay.co.uk/news/28''>28</a><br/>
<div class="article-content">

<h1 class="article">Theresa calls on Shanly to listen to local people on Badnell&acirc;&#128;&#153;s pit&nbsp;development</h1>


<p class="published"> 7 November 2006</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>Maidenhead MP Theresa May is calling on Michael Shanley to give local residents more time to comment on his plans to develop housing on Badnell&acirc;&#128;&#153;s Pit.</p>

	<p>Theresa explained, <em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;A lot of people told me they couldn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t get to the exhibition about Michael Shanley&acirc;&#128;&#153;s plans for Badnell&acirc;&#128;&#153;s Pit as it was only held for one day &acirc;&#128;&#147; and a week day at that! I am writing to Michael Shanley to make it clear to him that he cannot avoid the objections of local residents in this way. He must listen to local people. So I am calling on him to put the exhibition on again, for a longer period, ideally over a weekend, so many of the local residents who work during the week can see his plans and give him their views.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;What&acirc;&#128;&#153;s more I&acirc;&#128;&#153;m telling him that he mustn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t think that failure to attend the exhibition means people are happy with his plans. Far from it! Most people are aghast at the size of the development he is proposing which goes way beyond anything previously proposed.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;A development of 430 homes with 5 storey blocks of flats is simply unacceptable! It will bring the local roads to a standstill and put pressure on other services like schools and GPs&acirc;&#128;&#153; services.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;I have always felt strongly about the development of this site and I shall continue to campaign strongly on this issue with local residents. We need to ensure that we make the local voice heard.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;If you would like me to keep you informed about developments on this issue please contact me at House of Commons, London, SW1A 0AA, on 0207 219 1304 or <a href="mailto:mayt@parliament.uk">mayt@parliament.uk</a>&lsquo;</em>.</p>
</div>
<p class="article-category" style="display:none;">Uncategorized, </p>
</div>
<hr/>
<a href='http://www.tmay.co.uk/news/30''>30</a><br/>
<div class="article-content">

<h1 class="article">Theresa insists Shanly should listen to local&nbsp;people</h1>


<p class="published">28 November 2006</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>Developer Michael Shanly has rejected local MP Theresa May&acirc;&#128;&#153;s request for another exhibition for local residents on his plans for developing Badnell&acirc;&#128;&#153;s Pit.</p>

	<p>Theresa explained, <em>&acirc;&#128;&#152;I wrote to Michael Shanly on November 7th after a number of local residents told me that they couldn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t get to the exhibition about his plans for Badnell&acirc;&#128;&#153;s Pit because it was held only on one day and a weekday at that.&Acirc;&nbsp; That meant they couldn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t ask questions about his plans or give their views. I pressed him for a further exhibition to be held, over a weekend, to allow local people to make their views known.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;Now he&acirc;&#128;&#153;s replied ruling out any further exhibition period and saying I must have been &acirc;&#128;&#156;incorrectly briefed&acirc;&#128;&#157;.&Acirc;&nbsp; I wasn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t briefed by anyone on this. Unlike him I talk to local people and hear their views direct. &Acirc;&nbsp;I am appalled that he is refusing to take into account the wishes of many local residents who are concerned that his development will severely alter the area and their quality of life.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;I can only assume that he doesn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t want to give more people the chance to comment on his plans because he knows that his proposed development of 430 homes with 5 storey blocks of flats will be unacceptable to local residents. It will bring the local roads to a standstill and put pressure on other services like schools and GPs&acirc;&#128;&#153; services.</em></p>

	<p><em>&lsquo;I only hope he doesn&acirc;&#128;&#153;t try to claim that there were so few people at the exhibition that his plans are supported. He is not fooling anyone, and the people of Maidenhead will not accept his refusal to consult them.&rsquo;</em></p>

	<p>If you will be affected by Michael Shanly&acirc;&#128;&#153;s proposed development of Badnells Pitt and would like further consultation on his proposals please feel free to contact me at The House of Commons, London, SW1A 0AA, 0207 219 1304 or at <a href="mailto:mayt@parliament.uk">mayt@parliament.uk</a>.</p>
</div>
<p class="article-category" style="display:none;">Housing and development, Environment</p>
</div>
