<h1 class="article">Theresa re-elected as MP for&nbsp;Maidenhead</h1>


<p class="published"> 8 May 2015</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>Theresa May has been re-elected as MP for Maidenhead at the General Election. Theresa won 66% of the vote, giving her a majority of 29,059 &ndash; an increase from 16,769 in 2010. Speaking as the result was announced, she said: &ldquo;I am very pleased but hugely grateful to voters in Maidenhead who have done me this tremendous honour. I hope it is because I make every effort I can to work hard for the local constituency and take up issues that matter to people in Maidenhead such as the town centre, the train services and retaining services at St Mark&acirc;&#128;&#153;s Hospital and schools.&rdquo;</p>

	<p>&ldquo;My pledge is to continue to work hard for the constituency to ensure I represent people as I hope they wish to be represented.&rdquo;
 </p>
</div>
<p class="article-category" style="display:none;">Westminster News, </p>
</div>
<hr/>
<a href='http://www.tmay.co.uk/news/306''>306</a><br/>
<div class="article-content">

<h1 class="article">Theresa thanks Maidenhead residents for their&nbsp;support</h1>


<p class="published">11 May 2015</p>


<div class="article-body">
	<p>Theresa May has thanked Maidenhead residents for their support after she was re-elected as a Member of Parliament. She said: &ldquo;I am delighted to have been re-elected as MP for Maidenhead with an increased majority. I would like to thank everyone who voted for me. I will work hard over the next five years to serve the people of the Maidenhead constituency, whether they voted for me or not.&rdquo; </p>

	<p>&ldquo;My priorities will be to secure jobs and investment particularly in Maidenhead town centre, to safeguard local services including at St Marks Hospital and our vital train links, and to protect the local area from inappropriate development. There is a lot of work to do and I am looking forward to getting on with the job.&rdquo;</p>
</div>
<p class="article-category" style="display:none;">Westminster News, </p>
</div>
